The user’s implementation differs from ours. Theirs creates a single class checking preset points, whereas ours is designed to handle polygons of any size or shape. We use multiple PolygonRegion objects to define distinct field zones.

If they wish to proceed, users must create arrays like Pose2d or Translation2d for every point in their polygon. For instance:
```
Translation2d[] yellowRegion = new Translation2d[]{
    new Translation2d(4.501, 6.176),
    new Translation2d(8.768, 8.000)
};
```
This represents a two-point "polygon," which when published via NT using StructArrayPublisher, would display as a line in AdvantageScope.

Our loading station zone uses this approach too, creating a triangle in the field’s corner with an array:
```
new Translation2d[]{  
    new Translation2d(0, 0),
    new Translation2d(0, 4),
    new Translation2d(4.5, 0),
    new Translation2d(0, 0)
};
```
